    },
    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "This function switches the display mode of the specified display. The operation is always synchronous; the function does not return until the mode switch is complete. Note that after switching, display parameters and addresses may change. "
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "The selected display mode persists for the life of the calling program. When the program terminates, the display mode automatically reverts to the permanent setting in the Displays panel of System Preferences."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "When changing the display mode of a display in a mirroring set, other displays in the mirroring set will be assigned a mode that's capable of mirroring the bounds of the display being adjusted. To avoid this automatic behavior, you can use the following procedure: call"
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/coregraphics/1455235-cgbegindisplayconfiguration"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ", call "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/coregraphics/1543535-cgconfiguredisplaymode"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " for each display to explicitly set the mode, and finally call "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/coregraphics/1454488-cgcompletedisplayconfiguration"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "level": 3,
          "type": "heading",
          "text": "Special Considerations",
          "anchor": "1679505"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "This deprecated function takes as a parameter a display mode dictionary. Starting in OS X v10.6, display mode dictionaries have been replaced by the "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "CGDisplayMode"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " opaque type."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
